i%2C%20the%20founders%20of%20Boxabl%2C%20standing%20inside%20a%20Casita.%3Cp%3EBoxabl%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EIn%20a%20filing%2C%20Boxabl%20acknowledges%20it%20is%20the%20subject%20of%20an%20SEC%20inquiry.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ESeveral%20former%20employees%20and%20a%20person%20with%20knowledge%20of%20the%20company%20were%20interviewed%20by%20the%20agency.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EBoxabl%20has%20bled%20red%20ink%20but%20earned%20millions%20of%20dollars%20for%20its%20father-and-son%20cofounders.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBoxabl%20has%20acknowledged%20that%20it%20is%20the%20subject%20of%20an%20inquiry%20by%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F1816937%2F000164460023000158%2FBXBOMandFinancials2.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eupdated%20financial%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboxabl-tiny-homes-securities-and-exchange-commission-sec-2023-9%5C%22%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20former%20employees%20of%20the%20company%20and%20a%20person%20with%20knowledge%20of%20its%20financial%20reporting%20had%20been%20contacted%20and%20interviewed%20by%20the%20federal%20regulator%20in%20recent%20weeks.%20Two%20of%20those%20people%20were%20subpoenaed%2C%20a%20step%20the%20SEC%20typically%20takes%20when%20it%20is%20conducting%20an%20investigation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20people%2C%20who%20did%20not%20want%20to%20be%20identified%20publicly%20because%20they%20had%20been%20instructed%20by%20the%20agency%20that%20the%20inquiry%20was%20confidential%2C%20said%20they%20were%20asked%20about%20Boxabl's%20business%20practices%2C%20the%20responsibilities%20and%20conduct%20of%20senior%20Boxabl%20executives%2C%20and%20several%20public%20crowdfunding%20rounds%20that%20were%20used%20by%20the%20company%20to%20raise%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20from%20the%20public.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20company%20is%20aware%20that%20it%20is%20the%20subject%20of%20inquiries%20from%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%2C%26quot%3B%20Boxabl%20stated%20in%20a%20filing%20for%20its%202022%20financial%20performance%20that%20was%20updated%20with%20the%20disclosure%20on%20September%2015.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoxabl%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboxabl-tiny-home-casita-production-governance-galiano-paolo-tiramani-spending-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecome%20a%20sensation%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20relatively%20nascent%20real%20estate%20crowdfunding%20business%2C%20raising%20more%20than%20%24150%20million%20since%202020%2C%20mostly%20from%20the%20public.%20The%20startup%2C%20based%20in%20North%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20rose%20to%20fame%20as%20a%20manufacturer%20of%20factory-made%2C%20prefabricated%20tiny%20homes%20that%20it%20has%20presented%20as%20a%20cheaper%20alternative%20to%20traditionally%20built%20housing.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20filings%2C%20the%20company%20describes%20its%20business%20prospects%20as%20boundless%2C%20with%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20potential%20revenue.%20But%20Boxabl%2C%20so%20far%2C%20has%20bled%20red%20ink%20and%20has%20faced%20scrutiny%20from%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20investors%2C%20customers%2C%20and%20former%20employees.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20also%20been%20the%20subject%20of%20at%20least%20one%20whistleblower%20complaint%20with%20the%20SEC.%20Greg%20Ehlers%2C%20a%20former%20chief%20operating%20officer%20at%20the%20company%20who%20left%20in%20September%202021%2C%20sued%20Boxabl%20in%20a%20Nevada%20state%20court%2C%20alleging%20that%20the%20company%20terminated%20him%20improperly%20as%20retaliation%20for%20filing%20a%20complaint%20with%20the%20federal%20regulator.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20case%2C%20Ehlers%20stated%20that%20the%20company%20wasn't%20truthfully%20disclosing%20the%20costs%20of%20manufacturing%20its%20homes%20and%20misrepresenting%20the%20viability%20of%20its%20business%20model%20to%20investors.%20Boxabl%20has%20marketed%20its%20units%2C%20which%20it%20calls%20Casitas%2C%20at%20around%20%2460%2C000%2C%20but%20Ehlers%20claimed%20in%20his%20case%20that%20the%20units%20cost%20more%20than%20%2475%2C000%20to%20build.%20Boxabl%20denied%20Ehlers'%20accusations%20in%20an%20answer%20to%20his%20complaint%2C%20and%20countersued%20him%2C%20saying%20that%20he%20breached%20his%20employment%20contract%2C%20lied%20to%20the%20company%20during%20his%20recruitment%2C%20and%20violated%20his%20fiduciary%20duty%20to%20the%20company.%20The%20case%20is%20currently%20scheduled%20to%20go%20to%20trial%20next%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20Leader%20Capital%2C%20a%20mutual-fund%20manager%20based%20in%20Portland%2C%20Oregon%2C%20sued%20Boxabl%20in%20a%20Nevada%20state%20court%20in%20September%2C%20accusing%20Boxabl%20of%20delaying%20the%20sale%20of%20shares%20it%20holds%20in%20the%20company.%20Leader%20had%20planned%20to%20sell%20its%20stock%2C%20according%20to%20the%20suit%2C%20for%20%240.57%20each%2C%20less%20than%20the%20%240.80%20share%20price%20that%20Boxabl%20has%20recently%20charged%20investors.%20The%20deal%2C%20which%20would%20have%20netted%20it%20%243.7%20million%2C%20fell%20apart%20because%20of%20the%20delay%2C%20it%20said.%20Boxable%20has%20not%20yet%20responded%20to%20the%20complaint.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20recent%20disclosure%2C%20Boxable%20appeared%20to%20attribute%20the%20SEC%20inquiry%20to%20its%20%26quot%3Bunconventional%20marketing%20of%20securities%20offerings%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bpending%20lawsuits%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20the%20company%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20in%20position%20to%20comment%20on%20any%20non-public%20inquires.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20SEC%20does%20not%20comment%20on%20the%20existence%20or%20nonexistence%20of%20a%20possible%20investigation%2C%26quot%3B%20Cory%20Jarvis%2C%20an%20SEC%20spokesman%2C%20wrote%20to%20Insider%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGaliano%20Tiramani%2C%20Boxabl's%2035-year%20old%20cofounder%20and%20director%20of%20marketing%2C%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20on%20the%20company's%20acknowledgement%20of%20the%20SEC%20inquiry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoxabl%20has%20been%20delayed%20in%20filing%20financial%20information%2C%20disclosing%20its%20full-year%20financial%20performance%20for%202022%20in%20August.%20The%20filing%20showed%20the%20company%20sustained%20a%20%2433%20million%20operating%20loss%20in%202022%2C%20double%20the%20previous%20year%20and%20has%20not%20yet%20received%20the%20regulatory%20approval%20to%20sell%20its%20homes%20in%20any%20state%20in%20the%20country.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20loss%2C%20Tiramani%20and%20his%2065-year%20old%20father%2C%20Paolo%2C%20who%20serves%20as%20Boxabl's%20CEO%2C%20raised%20their%20base%20salaries%20in%202023%20to%20%24595%2C000%20rom%20%24400%2C000.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20pair%20each%20sold%20off%20about%20%245%20million%20of%20stock%20in%20the%20company.%20They%20remain%20the%20majority%20shareholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboxabl-securities-and-exchange-commission-tiny-homes-sec-filing-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695670999000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63e2c28096242f0019e7d957%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboxabl-securities-and-exchange-commission-tiny-homes-sec-filing-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Boxabl's%20prefabricated%20homes%20could%20help%20the%20housing%20crunch.%20But%20the%20company%20has%20left%20a%20trail%20of%20disillusioned%20employees%2C%20investors%2C%20and%20customers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dgeiger%40businessinsider.com%20(Daniel%20Geiger%2CAlex%20Nico