to%20take%20place%20in%20the%20future%2C%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fchina%2Fscience%2Farticle%2F3235590%2Fchinas-batwoman-scientist-warns-another-coronavirus-outbreak-highly-likely%5C%22%3E%20South%20China%20Morning%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%C2%A0The%20virologist%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F22221751.2023.2225932%5C%22%3Erecent%20research%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20titled%20'Assessment%20and%20sero-diagnosis%20for%20coronaviruses%20with%20risk%20of%20human%20spillover'%20warned%20that%20the%20world%20must%20be%20prepared%20for%20another%20disease%2C%20just%20like%20COVID-19%2C%20because%20%26quot%3Bif%20a%20coronavirus%20caused%20diseases%20to%20emerge%20before%2C%20there%20is%20a%20high%20chance%20it%20will%20cause%20future%20outbreaks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20study%2C%20Ms%20Zhengli%20and%20colleagues%20from%20the%20Wuhan%20Institute%20of%20Virology%20evaluated%20the%20human%20spillover%20risk%20of%2040%20coronavirus%20species.%C2%A0They%20found%20that%20half%20of%20these%20species%20are%20''highly%20risky''.%20Of%20these%2C%20six%20are%20already%20known%20to%20have%20caused%20diseases%20that%20infected%20humans%2C%20while%20there%20is%20evidence%20that%20a%20further%20three%20caused%20disease%20or%20infected%20other%20animal%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E''It%20is%20almost%20certain%20that%20there%20will%20be%20future%20disease%20emergence%20and%20it%20is%20highly%20likely%20a%20%5Bcoronavirus%5D%20disease%20again%2C''%20the%20study%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20was%20based%20on%20an%20analysis%20of%20viral%20traits%2C%20including%20population%2C%20genetic%20diversity%2C%20host%20species%2C%20and%20any%20previous%20history%20of%20zoonosis%2C%20%3Cem%3ESCMP%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereported.%20Further%2C%20the%20study%20also%20identified%20hosts%20of%20the%20pathogen%20including%20natural%20hosts%20like%20bats%20and%20rodents%2C%20or%20possible%20intermediate%20hosts%20including%20camels%2C%20civets%2C%20pigs%2C%20or%20pangolins.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20other%20Chinese%20virologists%20dismissed%20the%20claims%2C%20while%20some%20others%20were%20reluctant%20to%20comment%20on%20Ms%20Zhengli's%20latest%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20another%20scientist%20from%20China's%20Centres%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20(CDC)%20told%20the%20publication%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20that%20''Chinese%20authorities%20are%20downplaying%20COVID-19%2C%20and%20some%20cities%20have%20stopped%20releasing%20infection%20data.''%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Wuhan%20Institute%20of%20Virology%20has%20been%20under%20increased%20scrutiny%2C%20with%20some%20US%20politicians%20promoting%20the%20theory%20that%20COVID-19%20originated%20from%20an%20accidental%20leak%20from%20the%20lab.%20However%2C%C2%A0the%20head%20of%20US%20intelligence%20said%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20for%20the%20claim%2C%20as%20per%20an%20AFP%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20May%20this%20year%2C%C2%A0World%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%20chief%20also%20remarked%20that%20the%20world%20must%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fworld-needs-to-be-prepared-for-the-next-pandemic-who-chief-4060971%5C%22%3Eget%20ready%20for%20the%20next%20pandemic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20''Disease%20X''%2C%20which%20might%20be%20%26quot%3Beven%20deadlier%26quot%3B%20than%20Covid-19.%C2%A0%20According%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Factivities%2Fprioritizing-diseases-for-research-and-development-in-emergency-contexts%5C%22%3EWHO%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Brepresents%20the%20knowledge%20that%20a%20serious%20international%20epidemic%20could%20be%20caused%20by%20a%20pathogen%20currently%20unknown%20to%20cause%20human%20disease%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20be%20a%20new%20agent%20-%20a%20virus%2C%20a%20bacterium%2C%20or%20a%20fungus%20-%20without%20any%20known%20treatments.%20The%20WHO%20started%20using%20the%20term%20in%202018.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20COVID-19%20began%20to%20spread%20across%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695661980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-05%2Fpuv25g0c_chinas-bat-woman-bloomberg-650_625x300_26_May_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchinas-top-virologist-warns-against-another-covid-like-pandemic-highly-likely-4423208%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20study%2C%20Shi%20Zhengli%20and%20colleagues%20from%20the%20Wuhan%20Institute%20of%20Virology%20evaluated%20the%20human%20spillover%20risk%20of%2040%20coronavirus%20species.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchinas-top-virologist-warns-against-another-covid-like-pandemic-highly-likely-4423208%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchinas-top-virologist-warns-against-another-covid-like-pandemic-highly-likely-4423208%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchinas-top-virologist-warns-against-another-covid-like-pandemic-highly-likely-4423208%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Will%20Axar%20Recover%20In%20Time%20For%20WC%3F%20Report%20Provides%20Massive%20Injury%20Update%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPace%20spearhead%20Jasprit%20Bumrah%20will%20be%20available%20for%20the%20third%20ODI%20against%20Australia%20after%20being%20given%20a%20one-match%20break%20but%20all-rounder%20Axar%20Patel%20will%20be%20given%20a%20few%20more%20days%20to%20recover%20from%20his%20quadricep%20tear%20ahead%20of%20the%20World%20Cup%2C%20BCCI%20sources%20said%20on%20Monday.%20While%20Ravichandran%20Ashwin%20has%20done%20decently%20in%20his%20two%20outings%2C%20the%20team%20management%20is%20still%20bullish%20about%20the%20fitness%20of%20Axar%2C%20the%20left-arm%20s