e%20panel%20also%20asked%20the%20Union%20education%20ministry%20to%20hold%20discussions%20with%20various%20educational%20institutions%20and%20their%20regulatory%20bodies%20to%20understand%20the%20problems%20in%20NEP%E2%80%99s%20implementation%20and%20what%20can%20be%20done%20to%20address%20these%20challenges.%20The%20committee%20has%20asked%20the%20ministry%20to%20apprise%20it%20of%20the%20findings%20after%20these%20consultations%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Feducation%2Fnational-education-policy-2020-multiple-entry-multiple-exit-option-may-not-work-well-for-india-house-panel%2Farticle67341734.ece%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20students%20and%20teachers%20raised%20apprehensions%20about%20the%20proposed%20exit%20and%20entry%20system.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20will%20reduce%20the%20value%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20degree%20and%20this%20is%20a%20way%20to%20produce%20cheap%20labour%20for%20the%20job%20market.%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20eyewash%20and%20we%20want%20the%20existing%20system%20to%20continue%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mayukh%20Biswas%2C%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20Students%20Federation%20of%20India%20(SFI)%20was%20quoted%20by%20the%20paper%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695629751000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F24164751%2F1599px-Indian_Students_4616.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fmultiple-entry-exit-points-under-nep-unfit-for-indian-education-system-parliamentary-panel%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CIf%20institutions%20allow%20multiple%20exits%2C%20it%20would%20be%20very%20difficult%20for%20the%20institutions%20to%20predict%20how%20many%20students%20would%20exit%20and%20how%20many%20would%20join%20midway%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20panel%20said%20in%20its%20report.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%