(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123651%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.36.43-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123651%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.36.43-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123651%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.36.43-PM-300x212.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123651%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.36.43-PM-1024x723.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674738%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22847%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELand%20pooled%20map%20for%20Sector-2%20Zone%20P-II.%20The%20area%20statement%20shows%20that%20though%20the%20sector%20has%20been%20able%20to%20pool%C2%A0%2087.8%25%20of%20land%2C%20only%2065.79%25%20of%20the%20total%20pooled%20land%20is%20contiguous.%20Source%3A%20DDA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20provisional%20notice%20issued%20to%20these%20three%20sectors%20was%20hailed%20as%20one%20of%20the%20big%20steps%20under%20the%20much-delayed%20land%20pooling%20exercise.%20Stakeholders%20have%20largely%20been%20advocating%20for%20the%20speedy%20implementation%20of%20the%20policy.%20Demarcating%20the%20sector%20boundary%20along%20with%20proposed%20roads%20and%20location%20of%20villages%2C%20DDA%20had%20installed%20signages%20in%20the%20proposed%20sectors.%20This%20further%20raised%20hope%20among%20the%20stakeholders.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123936%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.39.26-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123936%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.39.26-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123936%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.39.26-PM-300x221.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25123936%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-12.39.26-PM-1024x755.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674771%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22885%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EProposed%20Sector%202%20Zone%20P-II%20map%20installed%20on%20a%20display%20board%20in%20the%20Tigipur%20village.%C2%A0Photo%3A%20Ritesh%20Rana%2C%20Bakhtawarpur%20village%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20there%20have%20been%20discussions%20going%20on%20to%20amend%20the%20Delhi%20Development%20Act%2C%201957%2C%20to%20make%20land%20pooling%20mandatory%20for%20those%20landowners%20who%20have%20not%20expressed%20willingness%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20policy%20if%20minimum%2070%25%20criteria%20is%20achieved.%20These%20amendments%20were%20announced%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Affairs%20minister%2C%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Puri.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20amendments%20are%20in%20contravention%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98voluntary%20participation%20clause%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20policy%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20non-democratic%20and%20participatory%20principles%20of%20any%20land%20policy.%20After%20issuing%20conditional%20notices%2C%20the%20DDA%20held%20public%20meetings%20in%20the%20month%20of%20July%202022%20in%20the%20villages%20of%20Sector%202%20and%20Sector%203%20on%20the%20land%20pooling%20policy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20DDA%20till%20date%20has%20provided%20four%20extension%20notices%20to%20the%20all%20the%20three%20sectors%20to%20form%20the%20consortium.%20The%2090-day%20deadline%20is%20long%20gone.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20latest%20notice%20issued%20by%20DDA%20mentioned%20the%20extension%20up%20to%20March%2031%2C%202023%2C%20for%20three%20sectors.%20However%2C%20even%20after%20five%20months%20of%20the%20deadline%2C%20no%20consortium%20has%20been%20formed%20in%20these%20three%20sectors.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20DDA%20has%20issued%20provisional%20notices%20to%2010%20other%C2%A0%20sectors%20across%20different%20zones.%20It%20has%20also%20conveyed%20through%20a%20public%20notice%20that%20in%20Sector%208B%20in%C2%A0%20Zone%20P-II%2C%20a%20consortium%20was%20registered%20on%20February%2027%2C%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20unclear%20as%20to%20why%20this%20delay%20is%20taking%20place%20in%20forming%20the%20consortiums.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25130757%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-1.07.41-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221104%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25130757%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-1.07.41-PM.png%201104w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25130757%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-1.07.41-PM-276x300.png%20276w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25130757%2FScreenshot-2023-09-25-at-1.07.41-PM-942x1024.png%20942w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-675030%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENotice%20regarding%20extension%20of%20time%20period%20to%20form%20consortium%20issued%20by%20DDA.%20Source%3A%20DDA%2C%20Land%20Pooling%C2%A0website%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20significant%20challenges%20in%20the%20formation%20of%20consortium%20is%20the%20small%20parcels%20of%20land%20is%20multiplicity%20of%20ownership.%20For%20instance%2C%20details%20of%20registered%20applicants%20who%20have%20shown%20willingness%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20policy%20from%20Sector%202%20Zone%20P-II%20points%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20majority%20of%20the%20landowners%20own%20land%20less%20than%20one%20hectare.%20With%20varied%20interests%20and%20each%20landowner%20trying%20to%20reap%20maximum%20benefits%20from%20the%20land%20pooling%20policy%2C%20there%20has%20been%20significant%20mistrust%20among%20landowners%20too.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESanjay%20Thakran%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20broker%20from%20Sector%2010A%20Zone%20N%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMaking%20the%20consortium%20is%20the%20biggest%20issue.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20are%20saying%20that%20one%20person%20will%20represent%20us%20and%20submit%20papers%20to%20the%20DDA.%20Now%2C%20if%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20someone%2C%20why%20would%20I%20give%20them%20charge%20of%20my%20land%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fthe-missing-villagers-of-the-ddas-green-development-policy%5C%22%3EThe%20Missing%20Villagers%20of%20the%20DDA%E2%80%99s%20Green%20Development%20Policy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20DDA%20says%20to%20first%20form%20a%20group%20of%20100-150%20people%20and%20then%20submit%20one%E2%80%99s%20land%20to%20some%20builder.%20Now%20a%20farmer%E2%80%99s%20concern%20is%20what%20will%20he%20do%20if%20the%20builder%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20take%20any%20action.%20DDA%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20give%20any%20money%20to%20the%20landowners.%20Our%20say%20is%20that%20either%20you%20scrap%20this%20consortium%20formation%20clause%20or%20else%20bring%20people%20together%20on%20this.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20announcement%20by%20DDA%20for%20the%20provisional%20notice%20was%20also%20seen%20as%20a%20major%20step%20that%20might%20impact%20the%20land%20prices%20in%20the%20villages.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMultiple%20interactions%20with%20landowners%20in%20land%20pooling%20villages%20have%20pointed%20to%20the%20steep%20rise%20and%20decline%20in%20land%20prices%20due%20to%20sudden%C2%A0%20announcements%20by%20authorities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20landowner%20from%20Sector%202%20Zone%20P-II%2C%20on%20the%20consortium%20notice%20by%20DDA%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202010-2011%20when%20discussions%20around%20the%20policy%20were%20happening%2C%20the%20rate%20was%20Rs%204-4.5%20crore%20per%20acre%20of%20land.%20Now%20it%20has%20gone%20down%20to%20Rs%201%20crore%20per%20acre.When%20the%20consortium%20notice%20came%2C%20the%20land%20prices%20should%20have%20increased%20to%20Rs%2010%20crore%20per%20acre%20and%20builders%20should%20have%20come%20in%20their%20cars%20inside%20the%20village%20with%C2%A0%20cash%20to%20purchase%20the%20land%20but%20there%20is%20no%20life%20in%20the%20policy.%20Why%20would%20investors%20come%20and%C2%A0%20invest%3F%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERTI%20correspondence%20with%20DDA%20and%20MoHUA%20has%20revealed%20that%20this%20policy%20has%20been%20reviewed%20and%20discussed%20in%20the%20PMO.%20But%20till%20date%20nothing%20has%20been%20finalised.%20The%20reply%20received%20two%20months%20ago%20stated%20that%20the%20matter%20is%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cexamination%20stage%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20the%20DDA%20has%20been%20historically%20blamed%20for%20the%20lack%20of%20trust%20among%20landowning%20villagers%2C%20with%20private%20players%20entering%20the%20policy%2C%20the%20landowners%20need%20an%20informed%20decision-making%20platform%20to%20come%20together.%20This%20is%20something%20that%20will%20not%20come%20about%20in%20the%20course%20of%20one%20or%20two%20meetings.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EParas%20Tyagi%20is%20president%20of%20Centre%20for%20Youth%20Culture%20Law%20and%20Environment%20(CYCLE)%2C%20a%20Delhi%20based%20non-profit%20organisation.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695629672000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25134124%2F9125819359_cc40fa1841_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fdelhi-land-pooling-policy-dda%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20DDA%20has%20been%20historically%20blamed%20for%20the%20lack%20of%20trust%20among%20Delhi's%20landowning%20villagers.%20One%20of%20its%20newer%20land%20pooling%20policy%20clauses%20deepens%20these%20divides.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fdelhi-land-pooling-policy-dda%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hollywood%20Writers%20Reach%20Tentative%20Deal%20With%20Studios%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13155533%2FF02TdGIaYAAm33K.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fhollywood%2Ft-37195247%5C%22%3EHollywood%3C%2Fa%3E%20writers%20reached%20a%20tentative%20labour%20agreement%20with%20the%20major%20studios%20on%20Sunday%2C%20the%20Writers%20Guild%20of%20America%20(WGA)%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20brief%20statement%2C%20the%20WGA%20said%20the%20agreement%20was%20%E2%80%9Cmade%20possible%20by%20the%20enduring%20solidarity%20of%20WGA%20members%20and%20extraordinary%20support%20of%20our%20union%20siblings%20who%20joined%20us%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fhollywood-writers-to-go-on-strike-over-pay%2Fa-65488752%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20picket%20lines%20for%20over%20146%20days.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20three-year%20contract%20must%20be%20approved%20by%20members%20of%20the%20Writers%20Guild%20of%20America%20(WGA)%2C%20which%20represents%2011%2C500%20film%20and%20television%20writers%2C%20before%20it%20can%20take%20effect.%20The%20terms%20of%20the%20deal%20were%20not%20immediately%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EActors%20are%20still%20on%20strike%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20deal%20is%20expected%20to%20end%20one%20of%20two%20strikes%20that%20have%20halted%20most%20film%20and%20television%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20nightly%20network%20shows%20such%20as%20NBC%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Tonight%20Show%20Starring%20Jimmy%20Fallon%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20ABC%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EJimmy%20Kimmel%20Live!%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0could%20return%20to%20the%20air%20within%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20writers%20prepare%20to%20possibly%20crack%20open%20their%20laptops%20again%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fhollywood-strike-shows-films-youll-have-to-wait-for%2Fa-66227440%5C%22%3Eit%E2%80%99s%20far%20from%20business%20as%20usual%20in%20Hollywood%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20actors%E2%80%99%20strike%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETalks%20between%20the%20studios%20and%20the%20striking%20actors%20have%20not%20yet%20resumed%2C%20so%20crew%20members%20left%20out%20of%20work%20by%20the%20walkout%20will%20remain%20unemployed%20for%20the%20time%20being.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20on%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftop-stories%2Fs-9097%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flogs1279.xiti.com%2Fhit.xiti%3Fs%3D531599%26s2%3D2%26p%3Dthewire.in%3A%3AVolltexte%3A%3Athewire.in_Volltexte_JS%26di%3D%26an%3D%26ac%3D%26x1%3D1%26x2%3D2%26x5%3Dthewire.in_Volltexte_JS%26x6%3D1%26x8%3Den-VAS-Volltexte-JavaScript-thewire.in-dwde%26x10%3Dthewire.in%3A%3AVolltexte%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695628847000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F13155533%2FF02TdGIaYAAm33K.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fhollywood-writers-reach-tentative-deal-with-studios%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Striking%20writers%20will%20go%20back%20to%20work%20if%20the%20deal%20is%20approved%20by%20union%20members.%20Actors%20are%20still%20on%20strike%20over%20compensation%2C%20residual%20payments%20and%20AI%20protection%2C%20among%20other%20issues.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fhollywood-writers-reach-tentative-deal-with-studios%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20Number%20of%20Salaried%20Workers%20Rise%20in%20India%2C%20So%20Does%20Inequality%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F13160830%2FRajasthan-NREGA-workers.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20the%20growth%20of%20the%20economy%20since%20the%201980%E2%80%99s%20has%20pulled%20millions%20of%20workers%20out%20of%20agriculture%20and%20led%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20regular%20wage%20workers%2C%20this%20has%20not%20benefited%20everyone%20equally%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2Fstate-of-working-india%2Fswi-2023%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efinds%20a%20report%20by%20Azim%20Premji%20University.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESC%2FST%20communities%20and%20religious%20minorities%20underrepresented%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98State%20of%20Working%20India%202023%3A%20Social%20Identities%20and%20Labour%20Market%20Outcomes%E2%80%99%20finds%20that%20while%20growth%20created%20regular%20wage%20jobs%20for%20all%20castes%2C%20the%20rates%20differed%20significantly.%20There%20has%20been%20a%20rise%20in%20SC%20regular%20wage%20workers%2C%20with%20around%2022%25%20of%20SC%20workers%20being%20regular%20wage%20as%20compared%20to%2032%25%20of%20others%2C%20but%2040%25%20of%20SC%20workers%20were%20in%20casual%20employment%20as%20compared%20to%20only%2013%25%20for%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUpward%20mobility%20has%20increased%20and%20caste%20based%20segregation%20has%20decreased%2C%20and%20yet%20entrepreneurs%20belonging%20to%20SC%20and%20ST%20communities%20are%20still%20rare.%20SC%20and%20ST%20owners%20are%20underrepresented%20compared%20to%20their%20percentage%20of%20the%20total%20workforce%2C%20even%20in%20the%20smallest%20firms%2C%20while%20the%20overrepresentation%20of%20upper%20castes%20rises%20with%20the%20size%20of%20the%20firm.%20SC%2FST%20owners%20are%20more%20uncommon%20in%20larger%20firms.%20Owners%20of%20companies%20with%20more%20than%2020%20employees%20are%20hardly%20SC%20or%20ST.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20points%20out%20that%20while%20structures%20of%20employment%20vary%20more%20with%20reference%20to%20gender%20and%20caste%2C%20religious%20identities%20have%20played%20an%20important%20role%20as%20well.%20During%20the%20course%20of%20the%20four-decade%20period%20since%20the%2080s%2C%20after%20adjusting%20for%20education%2C%20household%20size%2C%20state%2C%20and%20other%20pertinent%20criteria%2C%20Muslims%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20hold%20regular%20wage%20jobs%20and%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20in%20own-account%20or%20casual%20pay%20work.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.minorityaffairs.gov.in%2FWriteReadData%2FRTF1984%2F7830578798.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Sachar%20Committee%20Report%20from%202006%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20made%20note%20of%20the%20chronic%20underrepresentation%20in%20regular%20wage%20labour%2C%20which%20remains%20a%20huge%20cause%20for%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fin-bundelkhand-dirty-work-is-done-by-the-lower-caste-only%5C%22%3EIn%20Bundelkhand%2C%20%E2%80%98Dirty%20Work%E2%80%99%20Is%20Done%20Only%20by%20the%20Lower%20Caste%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWomen%20face%20stereotypes%2C%20pay%20gaps%20and%20discrimination%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGender%20based%20earning%20disparities%20have%20also%20reduced%20since%202017%2C%20but%20remain%20prominent%20%E2%80%93%20women%20earn%2076%25%20of%20what%20men%20do%2C%20and%20SC%2FST%20women%20earn%2054%25%20of%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20women%E2%80%99s%20pay.%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Workforce%20Population%20Rate%20(WPR)%20has%20risen%2C%20due%20to%20a%20rise%20in%20self-employment%20caused%20by%20the%20pandemic%20and%20subsequent%20lockdown%2C%20female%20employment%20rates%20have%20increased%20since%202019.%2050%25%20of%20women%20were%20self-employed%20prior%20to%20COVID%2C%20which%20increased%20to%2060%25%20afterwards.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20self-employment%20earnings%20were%20just%2085%25%20of%20what%20they%20had%20been%20in%20the%20April-June%202019%20quarter%2C%20even%20two%20years%20after%20the%202020%20shutdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGender%20norms%20also%20play%20a%20heavy%20role%20in%20determining%20women%E2%80%99s%20employment%20status.%20The%20%E2%80%9Cmale%20breadwinner%E2%80%9D%20norm%2C%20in%20which%20husbands%20are%20regarded%20as%20the%20primary%20earners%20and%20females%20contribute%20to%20home%20money%20only%20when%20necessary%2C%20is%20a%20prevalent%20gender%20norm.%20The%20report%20finds%20that%20when%20the%20husband%E2%80%99s%20earnings%20are%20high%2C%20women%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20greater%20chance%20that%20wives%20will%20be%20employed%20when%20husbands%E2%80%99%20incomes%20climb%2C%20starting%20about%20Rs%2040%2C000%20per%20month.%20The%20report%20states%20that%20this%20trend%20might%20be%20the%20product%20of%20shifting%20social%20norms%20brought%20on%20by%20increased%20wealth%2C%20or%20it%20might%20be%20the%20effect%20of%20such%20husbands%20being%20paired%20with%20more%20educated%20wives%20who%20have%20preferences%20and%20possibilities%20to%20obtain%20better-paying%20jobs%2C%20pointing%20out%20how%20class%20and%20gender%20are%20barriers%20to%20obtaining%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPost-marriage%20life%20and%20rules%20remain%20a%20significant%20factor%20in%20determining%20women%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20work.%20Married%20women%20living%20in%20families%20where%20the%20mother-in-law%20is%20present%20but%20not%20employed%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20employed%20compared%20to%20households%20where%20there%20is%20no%20mother-in-law%20present%3B%20and%20daughters-in-laws%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20employed%20if%20the%20mother-in-law%20is%20also%20employed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20finds%20that%20women%20are%20employed%20in%20higher%20proportion%20in%20districts%20where%20domestic%20violence%20is%20more%20prevalent%2C%20which%20could%20be%20from%20the%20backlash%20effect%20%E2%80%93%20that%20because%20traditional%20gender%20roles%20are%20being%20challenged%2C%20working%20women%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20experience%20partner%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20rural%20areas%20of%20Karnataka%20and%20Rajasthan%2C%20women%E2%80%99s%20employment%20participation%20increased%20dramatically%20during%20the%20first%20five%20years%20of%20marriage.%20The%20majority%20of%20this%20employment%20was%20as%20self-employed%20farmers%20or%20as%20contributing%20family%20members.%20However%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20marriage%20or%20motherhood%20penalty%20indicates%20that%20this%20is%20work%20done%20out%20of%20compulsion%20in%20order%20to%20survive.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWomen%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20the%20workforce%20also%20varies%20across%20the%20different%20social%20groups%20within%20%E2%80%93%20in%202020%2C%20the%20WPR%20was%20lowest%20for%20Muslim%20women%2C%20at%20a%20despairing%2016.3%25.%20This%20points%20towards%20difficulty%20of%20mobility%20and%20opportunities%2C%20as%20well%20as%20possible%20discrimination%20by%20employers%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20gender%2C%20caste%20and%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EUnemployment%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20economic%20growth%20and%20employment%20creation%20are%20still%20only%20weakly%20related.%20The%20report%20indicates%20that%20policies%20favouring%20faster%20growth%20do%20not%20necessarily%20foster%20faster%20job%20creation.%20Between%202004%20and%202019%2C%20growth%20often%20led%20to%20respectable%20employment.%20The%20pandemic%2C%20which%20produced%20a%20bigger%20surge%20in%20distressed%20employment%2C%20interrupted%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20educational%20levels%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20is%20lower%20than%20it%20was%20before%20COVID.%20However%2C%20it%20continues%20to%20be%20above%2015%25%20for%20graduates%2C%20and%20more%20concerningly%2C%20it%20reaches%20a%20staggering%2042%25%20for%20graduates%20under%2025.%20Unemployment%20has%20fallen%2C%20but%20remains%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20points%20out%20the%20glaring%20discrimination%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20caste%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20religion%2C%20which%20prevent%20access%20to%20opportunities%20and%20play%20a%20role%20in%20low%20workforce%20participation%20rates%20and%20unemployment.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695628521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F13160830%2FRajasthan-NREGA-workers.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fas-number-of-salaried-workers-rise-in-india-so-does-inequality-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%98State%20of%20Working%20India%202023%3A%20Social%20Identities%20and%20Labour%20Market%20Outcomes%E2%80%99%20finds%20that%20while%20growth%20created%20regular%20wage%20jobs%20for%20all%20castes%2C%20the%20rates%20differed%20significantly.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fas-number-of-salaried-workers-rise-in-india-so-does-inequality-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Will%20Khalistan%20Issue%20Aid%20or%20Hinder%20Modi%20in%202024%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25130152%2FH20220429111448.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20India%20Cable%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%C2%A0a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%C2%A0The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3Eclick%20here%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20general%20elections%20for%20the%2016th%20Lok%20Sabha%20near%2C%20Canada%20has%20hurled%20at%20India%20the%20sensitive%20Khalistan%20issue%2C%20with%20Canadian%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20going%20public%20on%20the%20differences%20between%20the%20two%20governments%20over%20their%20respective%20perceptions%20of%20the%20anti-Modi%20agitation%20among%20the%20influential%20and%20numerically%20strong%20Sikh%20community%20in%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWill%20this%20Khalistan%20issue%20aid%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20bid%20or%20hinder%20his%20ambition%20to%20recapture%20power%20in%202024%3F%20Either%20way%2C%20Khalistan%2C%20which%20had%20died%20a%20rather%20quiet%20death%20by%20the%20beginning%20of%20this%20century%20as%20the%20people%20of%20Punjab%20became%20exhausted%20after%20two%20decades%20of%20Sikh%20militancy%2C%20appears%20to%20be%20snowballing%20into%20a%20bigger%20issue%2C%20with%20international%20ramifications%20this%20time.%20Besides%2C%20within%20days%20of%20the%20Modi%20extravaganza%20in%20the%20name%20of%20G20%2C%20Trudeau%20seems%20to%20have%20taken%20some%20of%20its%20shine%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%2C%20president%20of%20the%20Guru%20Nanak%20Sikh%20Gurdwara%20Sahib%2C%20Surrey%2C%20British%20Columbia%20also%20led%20the%20Khalistan%20Tiger%20Force%20(KTF)%20claims%20NIA%20which%20had%20announced%20a%20reward%20of%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20for%20information%20leading%20to%20his%20arrest.%20In%20June%20this%20year%2C%20two%20men%20gunned%20down%20Nijjar%20outside%20the%20gurdwara.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20India%2C%20Canada%20has%20the%20largest%20Sikh%20population%20and%20Sikhs%20enjoy%20financial%20and%20political%20influence%20there.%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20killing%20led%20to%20widespread%20protests%20and%20street%20demonstrations%20by%20the%20Sikh%20community%20and%20human%20rights%20activists%2C%20who%20accused%20Indian%20intelligence%20of%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20killing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETrudeau%2C%20who%20arrived%20in%20Delhi%20on%20October%208%20to%20attend%20the%20G20%20summit%2C%20told%20the%20Canadian%20Parliament%20on%20September%2018%20that%20he%20had%20taken%20up%20with%20Indian%20PM%20Modi%20allegations%20of%20the%20involvement%20of%20Indian%20agencies%20in%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20killing.%20During%20the%20three-day%20meet%2C%20this%20rather%20sour%20note%20was%20kept%20away%20from%20the%20media.%20But%20Trudeau%20was%20forced%20to%20stay%20back%20for%2036%20hours%20due%20to%20a%20technical%20snag%20in%20his%20official%20plane%2C%20while%20he%20skipped%20the%20official%20banquet%20in%20honour%20of%20foreign%20delegates.%20He%20declined%20the%20offer%20of%20an%20Indian%20VIP%20plane%20to%20fly%20him%20home%20and%20waited%20for%20the%20release%20of%20his%20own%20plane.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fglobal-press-views-on-india-canada-row-nijjar-allegations%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Prickly%20Nationalism%E2%80%99%3A%20From%20a%20G20%20High%20to%20a%20Post-Canada%20Low%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20quite%20some%20time%20now%2C%20a%20section%20of%20the%20Sikh%20diaspora%2C%20not%20just%20in%20Canada%20but%20also%20in%20US%2C%20Britain%20and%20Australia%2C%20has%20been%20mobilising%20support%20for%20Khalistan.%20India%20has%20been%20raising%20this%20through%20official%20channels.%20But%20that%20has%20not%20helped%20much%2C%20insofar%20as%20this%20section%20of%20the%20diaspora%20has%20been%20holding%20protest%20demonstrations%20against%20Modi%2C%20accusing%20him%20of%20majoritarianism%20and%20undermining%20the%20interests%20of%20all%20minorities%2C%20including%20Sikhs.%20They%20are%20throwing%20cold%20water%20on%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20and%20his%20alma%20mater%2C%20the%20RSS%E2%80%99s%2C%20attempts%20to%20project%20Sikhism%20not%20as%20a%20distinct%20religion%20but%20as%20a%20%3Cem%3Epanth%3C%2Fem%3E%20(subsidiary)%20of%20Hindus%2C%20causing%20indignation%20and%20outrage%20among%20the%20Sikh%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20economic%20implications%20from%20the%20current%20standoff.%2016%20lakh%20people%20of%20Indian%20origin%20constitute%203%25%20of%20the%20Canadian%20population.%20Additionally%2C%202.3%20lakh%20Indian%20youth%20are%20studying%20and%20looking%20for%20work%20in%20Canada.%20India%E2%80%99s%20total%20trade%20with%20Canada%20is%20worth%20US%2411.68%20billion%2C%20which%20includes%2030%25%20of%20the%20pulses%20imported%20in%20the%20last%20fiscal.%20Canadian%20pension%20funds%20have%20invested%20%2455%20billion%20in%20India.%20On%20September%2015%2C%20the%20Canadian%20government%20announced%20that%20it%20has%20put%20on%20hold%20the%20proposed%20October%20visit%20of%20a%20high-level%20trade%20delegation%20to%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20immediate%20concerns%20are%20political.%20The%20BJP%20presence%20in%20Punjab%20is%20negligible%2C%20except%20in%20alliance%20with%20the%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%20or%20piggybacking%20on%20Bollywood%20stars%20%E2%80%95%20earlier%20Vinod%20Khanna%2C%20and%20now%20Sunny%20Deol.%20So%20the%20Nijjar%20controversy%20will%20not%20weaken%20an%20already%20weak%20BJP%20in%20Punjab%20much%20further.%20However%2C%20Modi%20might%20be%20looking%20at%20reaping%20the%20Khalistan%20harvest%20in%20adjoining%20territories%20like%20Jammu%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20and%20Haryana%2C%20where%20the%20BJP%20appears%20a%20bit%20shaky.%20The%20BJP%20had%20labelled%20the%20year-long%20farmers%E2%80%99%20dharna%20on%20Delhi%20borders%20and%20their%20Republic%20Day%20entry%20into%20the%20national%20capital%20as%20a%20Khalistani%20conspiracy.%20But%20it%20had%20serious%20repercussions%20for%20Modi%2C%20who%20eventually%20capitulated%20on%20the%20three%20anti-farmers%20laws.%20Will%20the%20Khalistan%20issue%20win%20him%20political%20dividends%20this%20time%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFaraz%20Ahmad%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist%20based%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695627950000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25130152%2FH20220429111448.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkhalistan-issue-aid-or-hinder-modi-2024%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20BJP's%20presence%20in%20Punjab%20is%20negligible%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20may%20seek%20to%20reaping%20the%20Khalistan%20harvest%20in%20adjoining%20territories%20like%20Jammu%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20and%20Haryana.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkhalistan-issue-aid-or-hinder-modi-2024%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Only%206.6%20Million%20Frontline%20Jobs%20Created%20in%20FY23%20%E2%80%93%20A%20Decline%20of%2017.5%25%20From%20FY22%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F07%2F8391859530_aefbe96f68_b.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20number%20of%20frontline%20jobs%20created%20declined%2017.5%25%20year-on-year%20in%20fiscal%202022-23%20due%20to%20cautious%20hiring%20by%20companies%20amid%20macroeconomic%20headwinds%2C%20showed%20a%20report%20by%20frontline%20workforce%20management%20platform%20BetterPlace.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAbout%206.6%20million%20jobs%20were%20created%20in%20the%20last%20fiscal%20year%20as%20compared%20to%20eight%20million%20in%20FY22%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fjobs%2Fhr-policies-trends%2Ffrontline-job-creation-drops-17-5-per-cent-to-over-6-6-million-in-fy23-report%2Farticleshow%2F103914145.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20citing%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20frontline%20jobs%20include%20customer%20facing%20roles%20such%20as%20call%20centre%20workers%2C%20delivery%20personnel%2C%20marketing%20executives%2C%20sales%20and%20business%20development%20executives%20and%20housekeeping%20staff%20among%20others.%20These%20jobs%20are%20critical%20because%20the%20employees%20in%20these%20roles%20are%20often%20the%20face%20of%20the%20company.%20Their%20interactions%20with%20customers%20can%20significantly%20impact%20a%20company%E2%80%99s%20reputation%20and%20customer%20satisfaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20decline%20comes%20after%20companies%20went%20on%20a%20hiring%20spree%20after%20in%20FY22%20when%20businesses%20reopened%20after%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EData%20also%20showed%20that%20average%20monthly%20salaries%20for%20frontline%20workers%20decreased%20by%204.5%25%20to%20Rs%2021%2C700%20in%20FY23%2C%20%3Cem%3EMSN%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.msn.com%2Fen-in%2Fmoney%2Fnews%2Fnew-frontline-jobs-decline-17-5-in-fy23-study%2Far-AA1hczKF%3Focid%3Dfinance-verthp-feeds%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIFM%20%26amp%3B%20IT%20recorded%20the%20highest%20monthly%20average%20salaries%20at%20Rs%2025%2C700%20and%20salaries%20in%20this%20sector%20increased%20by%2017%25%20compared%20to%20FY22.%20It%20was%20followed%20by%20BFSI%20and%20logistics%20%26amp%3B%20mobility%2C%20offering%20salaries%20of%20Rs%2022%2C000%20and%20Rs%2021%2C800%20per%20month%2C%20respectively%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20hiring%20numbers%20may%20improve%20this%20year%20as%20the%20ongoing%20festive%20season%20is%20leading%20to%20a%20surge%20in%20demand%20for%20manpower%20with%20companies%20looking%20to%20hire%20a%20combination%20of%20on-roll%2C%20on%20third-party%20roll%2C%20and%20gig%20workers%20to%20meet%20the%20rise%20in%20consumption%2C%20Pravin%20Agarwala%2C%20cofounder%20and%20group%20CEO%20of%20BetterPlace%20told%20%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20in%20FY23%2C%20the%20logistics%20and%20mobility%20sector%20replaced%20e-commerce%20as%20the%20highest%20employment%20industry%20for%20frontline%20workers%20with%20total%20demand%20increasing%20by%20111%25%20during%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20sectors%20like%20retail%20and%20warehousing%2C%20companies%20are%20looking%20to%20hire%20more%20women%20gig%20workers%20as%20hiring%20women%20results%20in%20better%20efficiency.%20Attrition%20in%20men%20is%20higher%20than%20in%20women.%20Besides%2C%20companies%20are%20focusing%20on%20ESG%20(environmental%2C%20social%20and%20governance)%20goals%2C%E2%80%9D%20Agarwala%20told%C2%A0the%20%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20expects%20variablisation%20of%20workforce%20to%20increase%20going%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20gig%20jobs%20have%20continued%20to%20grow%20stronger%2C%20(permanent)%20frontline%20jobs%20have%20not%20grown%20so%20much%E2%80%A6%20the%20end%20of%20FY22%20and%20beginning%20of%20FY23%20showed%20positive%20growth%20in%20demand%20but%20slowly%2C%20employers%20reduced%20vacancies%20due%20to%20various%20reasons%20like%20slowdown%20in%20business%2C%20business%20losses%2C%20over-hiring%2C%20cost%20of%20hiring%2C%20etc%E2%80%A6%20most%20enterprises%20are%20looking%20to%20variablise%20their%20workforce%20cost%20by%20moving%20to%20a%20gig%20model%20of%20workforce%20management%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Fgig-jobs-continue-to-grow-stronger-in-tough-times%2Farticleshow%2F103914246.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695626148000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F07%2F8391859530_aefbe96f68_b.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fonly-6-6-million-frontline-jobs-created-in-fy23-a-decline-of-17-5-from-fy22-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20decline%20happened%20due%20to%20cautious%20hiring%20by%20companies%20amid%20macroeconomic%20headwinds%2C%20said%20a%20new%20report.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fonly-6-6-million-frontline-jobs-created-in-fy23-a-decline-of-17-5-from-fy22-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Their%20Masjid's%20Fate%20Now%20in%20the%20Court's%20Hands%2C%20Mathura's%20Muslims%20Feel%20an%20Everyday%20Oppression%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25112937%2FSEM1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMathura%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EExisting%20next%20to%20each%20other%20peacefully%20in%20Mathura%20are%20two%20religious%20structures%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Shahi%20Eidgah%20Masjid%20and%20the%20Shri%20Krishna%20Janmasthan%20temple.%20Between%20them%20is%20a%20police%20watchtower.%20Today%2C%20however%2C%20these%20markers%20of%20peace%20have%20turned%20into%20something%20less%20desirable.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20lane%20that%20leads%20us%20to%20the%20Eidgah%20is%20guarded%20by%20police%20and%20remains%20isolated%20unless%20it%20is%20time%20for%20%3Cem%3Enamaz%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Shops%20in%20the%20lane%20wear%20a%20look%20of%20enforced%20silence%2C%20with%20people%20barely%20making%20eye%20contact%20with%20outsiders.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20road%20leading%20to%20the%20Shri%20Krishna%20Janmasthan%20Temple%20complex%20is%20illuminated%20with%20lights%2C%20accommodating%20faces%20from%20all%20over%20India.%20A%20community%20of%20shops%20paves%20the%20way%20that%20leads%20you%20to%20the%20complex%2C%20which%20stands%20tall%20with%20confidence%20amid%20the%20communal%20chaos.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20sunset%20approaches%20Mathura%2C%20the%20Shri%20Krishna%20Janmasthan%20Temple%20complex%20shines%20through%20the%20darkness%2C%20with%20Hindu%20%3Cem%3Emantras%20%3C%2Fem%3Eechoing.%20But%20as%20darkness%20takes%20over%2C%20the%20Shahi%20Eidgah%20Masjid%20slips%20into%20a%20silent%20state%20of%20mourning.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDistanced%20in%20democracy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGuddo%20Khan%20and%20Mridula%20Singh%20had%20been%20best%20friends%20ever%20since%20they%20held%20each%20other%E2%80%99s%20hands%20on%20the%20first%20day%20of%20school%20when%20they%20were%20barely%20five%20and%20had%20joined%20the%20Kanya%20Prathmik%20School%20in%20Mathura.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20in%20class%208%20when%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20was%20martyred.%20What%20happened%20there%20spilled%20over%20to%20Mathura%20too%2C%20Mridula%20stopped%20talking%20to%20me.%20Even%20when%20Hindu%20%3Cem%3Ekarsevaks%3C%2Fem%3E%20toppled%20the%20Masjid%2C%20she%20thought%20Muslims%20were%20at%20fault%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Khan%2C%2044%2C%20who%20lost%20Singh%20as%20a%20friend%20forever%20after%C2%A0December%206%2C%201992.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20on%20December%208%2C%20three%20decades%20after%20Muslims%20lost%20the%20Masjid%20to%20fanaticism%20and%20hate%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fkrishna-janmabhoomi-shahi-idgah-dispute-mathura-court-to-hear-case-on-may-9-1213625.html%5C%22%3EBal%20Krishna%20through%20Hindu%20Sena%20chief%20Vishnu%20Gupta%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20others%20filed%20a%20suit%20in%20the%20court%20of%20Civil%20Judge%20Senior%20Division%20(III)%20for%20shifting%20the%20Shahi%20Eidgah%20Masjid.%20According%20to%20their%20claim%2C%20the%20masjid%20has%20been%20constructed%20on%20a%20part%20of%2013.37-acre%20land%20belonging%20to%20the%20Sri%20Krishna%20Janmabhoomi%20Trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioners%20argued%20that%20the%20mosque%20in%20Mathura%20was%20built%20on%20the%20orders%20of%20Emperor%20Aurangzeb%20adjacent%20to%20the%20Krishna%20Janmasthal%20%E2%80%94%20which%20some%20believe%20to%20be%20the%20place%20where%20the%20Hindu%20deity%20Krishna%20was%20born%20%E2%80%94%20after%20demolishing%20a%20temple.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20noose%20around%20the%20neck%20of%20Mathura%E2%80%99s%20Muslims%20has%20grown%20tighter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25113020%2FSEM2.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25113020%2FSEM2.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25113020%2FSEM2-300x169.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25113020%2FSEM2-1024x576.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-674676%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Shahi%20Eidgah%20Masjid%20and%20the%20Shri%20Krishna%20Janmasthan%20temple%20in%20Mathura.%20Photo%3A%20Tarushi%20Aswani%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMuslim-%3Cem%3Emukt%3C%2Fem%3E%20Mathura%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENizamuddin%20Azeem%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20streets%20leading%20to%20the%20Eidgah.%20The%20three-domed%20structure%20holds%20heaps%20of%20memories%20from%20his%20childhood%20Eids.%20Now%2C%20Azeem%20says%2C%20there%20is%20a%20stillness%20near%20the%20structure.%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20hesitate%20to%20spend%20much%20time%20here%2C%20they%20just%20pray%20and%20leave%2C%20as%20if%20something%20ominous%20will%20happen%20if%20they%20stay%20longer.%20This%20has%20happened%20since%20they%20claimed%20that%20the%20Eidgah%20is%20built%20on%20temple%20land%2C%E2%80%9D%20Azeem%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMehraj%20Alam%2C%20a%20BAMCEF%20(Backward%20and%20Minority%20Communities%20Employees%20Federation)%20worker%2C%20said%20that%20the%20whole%20controversy%20around%20the%20Eidgah%20was%20only%20to%20have%20a%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98Muslim-mukt%20Mathura%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Muslim-free%20Mathura)%E2%80%99.%20%E2%80%9CSuddenly%20they%20have%20problems%20with%20the%20place%20where%20Muslims%20pray%2C%20the%20food%20Muslims%20sell%20and%20consume.%20They%20are%20even%20using%20the%20law%20to%20favour%20their%20own%20narrative%20of%20what%20existed%20before%20which%20structure%2C%20to%20only%20martyr%20another%20mosque%20after%20Babri%2C%E2%80%9D%20Alam%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20stands%20out%20here%2C%20when%20one%20tries%20to%20understand%20the%20dispute%2C%20is%20the%20disturbing%20deployment%20of%20law%20to%20discern%20the%20true%20custodians%20of%20the%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Janmabhoomi%20Trust%20in%20Agra%20is%20challenging%20a%20compromise%20made%20in%20the%201960s%20between%20a%20temple%20body%20and%20the%20Shahi%20Masjid%20Eidgah%20over%20disputed%20land.%20The%20trust%20is%20claiming%20a%2013.37-acre%20tract%20of%20land%20next%20to%20to%20the%20Sri%20Krishna%20Janmabhoomi%20temple%20complex.%20Several%20suits%20have%20been%20filed%20saying%20that%20the%20Eidgah%20complex%20was%20built%20on%20land%20belonging%20to%20the%20Janmasthan%20Trust.%20The%20trust%20is%20now%20seeking%20a%20cancellation%20of%20the%20agreement%20made%20in%201968%20and%20a%20declaration%20that%20the%20land%20solely%20belongs%20to%20the%20Trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22%E2%80%98Scared%20to%20Buy%2C%20Eat%20Meat%E2%80%99%3A%20Muslims%20in%20Mathura%20After%20Arrests%20on%20Suspicion%20of%20Cow%20Slaughter%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fscared-to-buy-eat-meat-muslims-in-mathura-after-arrests-on-suspicion-of-cow-slaughter%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Scared%20to%20Buy%2C%20Eat%20Meat%E2%80%99%3A%20Muslims%20in%20Mathura%20After%20Arrests%20on%20Suspicion%20of%20Cow%20Slaughter%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20cancellation%20that%20the%20trust%20is%20seeking%20is%20based%20on%20an%20agreement%20undertaken%20by%20the%20Sri%20Krishna%20Janmabhoomi%20Seva%20Sangh%2C%20a%20body%20of%20the%20temple%20that%20was%20dissolved%20later.%20This%20agreement%20approved%20the%20passover%20of%20the%20contentious%20portion%20of%20land%20to%20the%20Eidgah%20committee%20in%201968.%20In%20its%20petition%2C%20the%20Trust%20has%20said%20that%20the%20deal%2C%20which%20was%20finalised%20before%20the%20civil%20judge%20(senior%20division)%2C%20Mathura%20in%201973-74%2C%20is%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20binding%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20temple%20as%20the%20Seva%20Sangh%20had%20%E2%80%9Cno%20authority%E2%80%9D%20to%20decide%20on%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Mohammed%20Iqbal%2C%20who%20represents%20the%20Shahi%20Eidgah%20committee%20in%20the%20case%2C%20believes%20that%20while%20no%20one%20had%20a%20problem%20with%20the%20coexistence%20of%20the%20structures%20for%20years%20together%2C%20problems%20have%20emerged%20after%20the%20politicisation%20of%20religious%20structures%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fayodhya-verdict-supreme-court-full-text%5C%22%3EAyodhya%20title%20dispute%20verdict%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20delivered.%20The%20Mathura%20mosque%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fshri-krishna-janmabhoomi-mathura-shahi-idgah-mosque-temple-supreme-court%5C%22%3Ethird%C2%A0after%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Ayodhya%20and%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Mosque%20in%20Varanasi%20that%20Hindutva%20organisations%20have%20claimed%20is%20illegal.%20Iqbal%20also%20said%20that%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20(Special%20Provisions)%20Act%2C%201991%20was%20being%20sidelined%20in%20this%20matter.%20The%20Act%20says%20that%20a%20mosque%2C%20temple%2C%20church%20or%20any%20place%20of%20public%20worship%20in%20existence%20on%20August%2015%2C%201947%20will%20retain%20the%20same%20religious%20character%20that%20it%20had%20on%20that%20day%20%E2%80%93%20irrespective%20of%20its%20history%20%E2%80%93%20and%20cannot%20be%20changed%20by%20the%20courts%20or%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fplaces-of-worship-act-ashwini-kumar-supreme-court-ayodhya%5C%22%3EPlaces%20of%20Worship%20Act%3A%20Is%20Supreme%20Court%20Unwittingly%20Helping%20Centre%20With%20Proxy%20Litigation%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Ready%20to%20retaliate%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMohammed%20Burhanuddin%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Eidgah%20committee%2C%20views%20the%20case%20against%20the%20Eidgah%20as%20an%20attempt%20to%20Hinduise%20Mathura%20more%20than%20the%20existing%20bans%20would%20ever%20be%20able%20to.%20%E2%80%9CMathura%20has%20mandirs%20and%20masjids.%20We%20respect%20that%20Hindus%20from%20across%20India%20come%20here%20for%20their%20religious%20purpose%2C%20but%20Mathura%20is%20ours%20too%2C%20we%20have%20lived%20along%20Hindus%20peacefully%20for%20centuries.%20Why%20is%20our%20existence%20being%20made%20into%20a%20court%20case%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20Muslims%20in%20the%20holy%20Hindu%20city%2C%20Burhanuddin%20questions%20the%20state%20and%20its%20decisions%20regarding%20Muslims%20every%20day.%20From%20the%20ban%20on%20the%20sale%20of%20meat%20to%20abrupt%20demolitions%20of%20Muslim%20homes%2C%20to%20their%20place%20of%20worship%20falling%20prey%20to%20Hindu%20%3Cem%3Erashtra%3C%2Fem%3E%20politics%20%E2%80%93%20Muslims%20in%20Mathura%20have%20a%20plethora%20of%20problems%20that%20surround%20their%20existence%20as%20a%20non-Hindu%20community%20in%20a%20territory%20holy%20to%20Hindus.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmid%20these%20questions%2C%20Vijay%20Bahadur%20Singh%2C%20public%20relations%20officer%2C%20Shri%20Krishna%20Janmasthan%20Temple%2C%20feels%20that%20Mathura%E2%80%99s%20glory%20will%20finally%20be%20restored%20once%20the%20%E2%80%98battle%E2%80%99%20for%20the%20Janmasthan%20is%20won.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22'They%20Bulldozed%20Our%20Life'%3A%20Mathura's%20Muslims%20Struggle%20as%20the%20State%20Crushes%20Their%20Homes%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fthey-bulldozed-our-life-mathuras-muslims-struggle-as-the-state-crushes-their-homes%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98They%20Bulldozed%20Our%20Life%E2%80%99%3A%20Mathura%E2%80%99s%20Muslims%20Struggle%20as%20the%20State%20Crushes%20Their%20Homes%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Trust%20has%20demanded%20that%20the%20mosque%2C%20which%20abuts%20the%20temple%2C%20be%20removed%20and%20the%20land%20returned%20to%20the%20Trust%2C%20Singh%20is%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20the%20mosque%20is%20nothing%20but%20a%20%E2%80%98structure%E2%80%99%20that%20has%20been%20illegally%20used%20by%20Muslims%20for%20decades%20to%20offers%20prayers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Singh%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3ESanatan%20dharma%3C%2Fem%3E%20teaches%20us%20to%20pick%20up%20arms%20for%20religion%2C%20and%20we%20have%20no%20problem%20in%20that%2C%20but%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20take%20this%20step.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESingh%20added%20that%20at%20any%20point%2C%20Hindus%20would%20not%20hesitate%20to%20retaliate%20if%20the%20situation%20called%20for%20it.%20He%20also%20said%20that%20if%20Muslims%20were%20keen%20to%20follow%20a%20rigid%20form%20of%20Islam%2C%20they%20are%20free%20to%20leave%20Mathura%20and%20practice%20it%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMandirs%20are%20no%20more%20a%20sign%20of%20amity%20for%20Mathura%E2%80%99s%20Muslims%20%E2%80%93%20instead%2C%20they%20are%20a%20symbolic%20reminder%20that%20their%20lives%20and%20livelihoods%20are%20being%20flattened%20in%20the%20name%20of%20Hinduism.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETarushi%20Aswani%20is%20an%20independent%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695625218000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F25112937%2FSEM1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmathura-muslims-shahi-eidgah-krishna-janmasthan%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ever%20since%20the%20verdict%20in%20the%20Ayodhya%20title%20dispute%20case%2C%20Muslims%20in%20Mathura%20believe%20the%20politicisation%20of%20religious%20structures%20has%20left%20them%20in%20an%20even%20more%20precarious%20state.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A27%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmathura-muslims-shahi-eidgah-krishna-janmasthan%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Skill%20Development%20Case%3A%20SC%20Refuses%20Urgent%20Mentioning%20of%20Naidu's%20Petition%20to%20Quash%20FIR%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F24143246%2Fnaidu.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Monday%20refused%20urgent%20mentioning%20of%20a%20petition%20filed%20by%20former%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20chief%20minister%20N.%20Chandrababu%20Naidu%20to%20quash%20the%20case%20registered%20against%20him%20in%20an%20alleged%20skill%20development%20scam.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fcome-tomorrow-supreme-court-refuses-to-take-up-chandrababu-naidus-plea-to-quash-fir-today-238599%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20petition%20was%20not%20included%20in%20the%20list%20of%20oral%20mentions%20for%20Monday.%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20refused%20out-of-turn%20listing%20to%20the%20petition%2C%20asking%C2%A0Naidu%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%20Siddharth%20Luthra%20to%20mention%20it%20again%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENaidu%20had%20filed%20a%20special%20leave%20petition%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Saturday%20challenging%20the%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20dismissal%20of%20his%20plea%20to%20quash%20the%20FIR.%20Subsequntly%2C%20a%20court%20in%20Vijayawada%20granted%20two%20days%E2%80%99%20police%20custody%20to%20the%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20Crime%20Investigation%20Department%20(CID)%20to%20interrogate%20Naidu.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday%2C%20with%20Naidu%E2%80%99s%20custody%20set%20to%20end%2C%20the%20Vijayawada%20ACB%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Fandhra-pradesh%2Fchandrababu-naidus-judicial-custody-extended-till-oct-5%5C%22%3Eextended%20it%20by%2011%20days%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20until%20October%205.%20The%20Telugu%20Desam%20Party%20(TDP)%20chief%20was%20produced%20before%20the%20court%20virtually%20from%20the%20Rajahmundry%20Central%20Jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnaidus-arrest-what-is-the-andhra-pradesh-skill-development-scam%5C%22%3Earrested%3C%2Fa%3E%20early%20on%20September%209%2C%C2%A0as%20an%20accused%20in%20the%20FIR%20registered%20by%20the%20AP%20CID%20in%202021%20over%20an%20alleged%20multi-crore%20scam%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20State%20Skill%20Development%20Corporation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20Naidu%E2%80%99s%20term%20(2014-19)%2C%20the%20state%20government%20and%20two%20companies%20initiated%20a%20project%20to%20create%20six%20centres%20of%20excellence%20(CoE)%20and%2036%20technical%20skill%20development%20institutes.%20The%20estimated%20cost%20was%20around%20Rs%203%2C281%20crore%2C%20which%20the%20CID%20claims%20is%20an%20inflated%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CID%20claims%20that%20Naidu%20and%20others%20allegedly%20routed%20hawala%20transactions%20through%20a%20network%20of%20shell%20companies%2C%20did%20not%20adhere%20to%20procedures%20and%20disregarded%20observations%20regarding%20the%20project%E2%80%99s%20viability.%20The%20TDP%20has%20set%20up%20a%20website%20to%20counter%20the%20allegations%2C%20highlighting%20that%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20established%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20numbers%20of%20clusters%20and%20trained%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20candidates%20among%20all%20the%20states%20that%20had%20similar%20schemes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20high%20court%20had%20dismissed%20Nadiu%E2%80%99s%20petition%20to%20quash%20the%20case%20while%20noting%20that%20the%20investigation%20is%20attaining%20finality%20and%20the%20court%20cannot%20interfere%20at%20this%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENaidu%E2%80%99s%20arguments%20in%20SC%20petition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Naidu%E2%80%99s%20petition%20in%20the%20top%20court%20says%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Csuddenly%20named%20in%20the%20FIR%E2%80%9D%20and%20arrested%20in%20an%20illegal%20manner%20for%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%20reasons%E2%80%9D.%20While%20claiming%20that%20due%20process%20was%20not%20followed%20before%20his%20arrest%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20seeking%20mandatory%20approval%20under%20Section%2017-A%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act%2C%201988%2C%20the%20plea%20states%20that%20the%20FIR%20is%20a%20case%20of%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%20vendetta%E2%80%9D.%20Naidu%20and%20his%20family%20%E2%80%9Care%20being%20targeted%20to%20crush%20all%20opposition%20to%20the%20party%20in%20power%20in%20the%20Respondent%20State%20with%20elections%20coming%20near%20in%202024%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20petition%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20also%20accused%20the%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20CID%20of%20acting%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20the%20ruling%20party%20to%20damage%20the%20TDP%E2%80%99s%20prospects%20in%20the%20state%20assembly%20election%2C%20which%20are%20scheduled%20to%20be%20held%20parallel%20to%20the%20general%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20CID%20is%20threatening%20the%20officers%20and%20others%20to%20implicate%20the%20Petitioner%2C%20his%20family%20and%20the%20Party.%20The%20continuing%20political%20vendetta%20by%20the%20State%20Administration%20is%20demonstrated%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20various%20senior%20leaders%20of%20the%20Petitioner%E2%80%99s%20party%20have%20in%20the%20past%20been%20arrested%20and%20now%20hastily%20are%20being%20sought%20to%20be%20implicated%20in%20false%20cases%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20petition%20says%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695624909000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F24143246%2Fnaidu.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fskill-development-case-sc-refuses-urgent-mentioning-naidu-petition%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20separate%20development%20on%20Sunday%2C%20the%20Vijayawada%20ACB%20court%20extended%20the%20former%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20chief%20minister's%20police%20custody%20by%2011%20days%2C%20until%20October%205.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fskill-development-case-sc-refuses-urgent-mentioning-naidu-petition%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20loosening%20its%20planned%20restrictions%20on%20laptop%2C%20tablet%20imports%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695623450000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-09%2F25%2Ffull%2F1695623087-6747.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Findia-loosening-its-planned-restrictions-on-laptop-tablet-imports-123092500306_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20part%20of%20the%20latest%20plan%2C%20all%20companies%20bringing%20eve